# Chapter 5: Technologies Used

### Snort 3

Snort 3 is an open-source Network Intrusion Detection and Prevention System capable of performing deep packet inspection using customizable detection rules.

### Ubuntu Linux

Ubuntu provides a stable and secure environment for installing and configuring Snort.

### Kali Linux

Kali Linux was used as the attacking machine to generate test traffic.

### Nmap

Nmap was used to simulate TCP SYN scan attacks.

### AFPacket

AFPacket enables Snort to operate in inline IPS mode, allowing malicious packets to be dropped before reaching the destination.

