# Chapter 7: IDS Implementation

In IDS mode, Snort passively monitors network traffic without modifying packets.

The following attacks were successfully detected:

* ICMP Ping
* TCP SYN Scan

Detection was performed using custom alert rules stored in the local.rules file.

---

# Chapter 8: IPS Implementation

Snort was configured in inline mode using AFPacket.

Custom drop rules were used to prevent malicious ICMP packets from reaching the target system.

During testing, Snort successfully blocked ICMP packets and generated drop alerts confirming prevention.

